    "body": "here's how it happened after I turned on some debugs\r\n+ last processed block is 174071: `2020-12-25 16:14:41 [CHAIN]           ^[[34mdebug^[[39m: Block processed slot=174071, root=0x8e85d480980d6b633fb2cece5686457bb5293f872e291d217280709a2fc01d4d`\r\n+ gossip block 174072 came and failed with `BLOCK_ERROR_FUTURE_SLOT` error: `2020-12-25 16:14:46 [NETWORK]          ^[[33mwarn^[[39m: Ignoring gossip block blockRoot=0xa2fc72f28775abfee38fb32d101cecbdda1ad530dd7e2b15254f57c07632fac6, blockSlot=174072 code=BLOCK_ERROR_FUTURE_SLOT, currentSlot=174071, blockSlot=174072`\r\n+ `eventHandlers` handled that error and add to pending block pool using `addBySlot`\r\n+ immediately after that, it's time for slot 174072 but surprisingly it showed no pending block for slot 174072\r\n```\r\n 2020-12-25 16:14:47 [CHAIN]         ^[[36mverbose^[[39m: Clock slot slot=174072\r\n 592935 2020-12-25 16:14:47 [CHAIN]           ^[[34mdebug^[[39m: Block pools:  pendingBlocks=0, currentSlot=174072\r\n```\r\n\r\nfrom this time node keeps finding missing block root which is 174071 and it found that block quickly but then it failed with `BLOCK_ERROR_BLOCK_IS_ALREADY_KNOWN` since that block was really processed\r\n```\r\n2020-12-26 07:26:59 [SYNC]          verbose: Finding block for unknown ancestor root blockRoot=0x8e85d480980d6b633fb2cece5686457bb5293f872e291d217280709a2fc01d4d\r\n...\r\n2020-12-26 07:28:15 [SYNC]          verbose: Found block for root slot=174071, blockRoot=0x8e85d480980d6b633fb2cece5686457bb5293f872e291d217280709a2fc01d4d\r\n...\r\n2020-12-26 07:31:02 [CHAIN]           debug: Block error code=BLOCK_ERROR_BLOCK_IS_ALREADY_KNOWN\r\n```\r\nthe above logs have happened forever ...",
